    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1999 Porsche 911 Carrera features the 3.4L flat-six M96 powerplant, delivering linear power through a crisp 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. The chassis maintains its factory-spec geometry with MacPherson struts and a precision-engineered multi-link rear setup, providing exceptional lateral grip and communicative hydraulic steering feedback. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a proactive IMS bearing retrofit and a cooling system refresh with a high-flow water pump. The braking system utilizes four-piston monoblock calipers over vented rotors, ensuring consistent thermal management. This is a mechanically sound example of the 996.1 generation, offering a visceral, analog driving experience.",
